When you buy a lottery ticket, you don't have any guaranteed chance that you'll win.  When you lose, you don't storm into 7-11 and demand your money back, either.  When you pay a lawyer for his services, you don't demand legal fees refunded when you lose the case.  A lawyer's mentality would be that they went through law school, went through thousands of dollars worth of tuition, he's deserved his money for his services.  The same with the jeweller's.  They've gone through hours upon hours and thousands of plat to get to where they are, they've deserved the profit.<br>
